<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:56PM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Monroe
and east central Clarke Counties through 345 PM CDT...
At 255 PM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm 9 miles east of Whatley, or 13 miles east of
Grove Hill. This storm was nearly stationary. Some rotation is being
noted on radar and will need to be closely monitored.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Monroe and east central Clarke Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
